\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. O. corsica} (Loisel.) G. Don fil., {\i Gen. Syst.}{\b  4}: 611 (1838). Scabrid-strigulose annual. Stems 8-15(-25) cm, procumbent, branched from the base. Leaves 6-10 mm, linear-oblong, obtuse. Inflorescences 1-2 cm, fairly dense; bracts 4-7 mm, linear-lanceolate; pedicels 1-2 mm. Calyx 4-5 mm; teeth triangular, obtuse. Corolla 5-6 mm, yellow (rarely white), pubescent; lower lip more or less porrect. Anthers glabrous, included. Capsule 4-5 mm, obovate, pubescent.{\i  Rocky mountain pastures.• Corse, Sardegna.} Co Sa.
