\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. O. verna} (Bellardi) Dumort.,{\i  Fl. Belg.} 32 (1827) ({\i O. rubra} Besser). Appressed-pubescent to strigulose annual. Stem 10-50 cm, erect or ascending, somewhat 4-angled, simple or branched. Leaves 12-40 × 3-8 mm, lanceolate, crenate to serrate, rarely subentire. Inflorescences 3-10 cm, rather lax; flowers subsessile. Calyx 5-8 mm; teeth triangular, obtuse. Corolla 8-10 mm, pubescent, reddish-pink (rarely white); tube 5-6 mm; lower lip somewhat deflexed. Anthers glabrous, more or less exserted. Capsule 6-8 mm, oblong, pubescent. {\i Meadows, pastures, roadsides, cultivated fields and other disturbed habitats. Most of Europe, but absent from some of the islands.} All except Az Bl Cr Fa Is Sa Sb.
\par

